Matter before the Court for Sentencing Hearing.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 8 MONTHS IN THE HOUSE OF CORRECTION with Huber privileges, credit for 4 days time served.  Th Court objects to Electronic Monitoring.

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 1 YEAR with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Attend and successfully complete Anger management and Parenting class;
* No illegal drugs; agent to assess AODA needs;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory costs, surcharges, fees, and assessments, by the end of probation period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;

The Court ordered restitution set at zero.  Appeal rights given by the Court. 
